	<a name="startcontent"></a>
	<h1>Irish passport card</h1>
	
<ul class="anchorlinks"><li><a href="#l0b797">Introduction</a></li><li><a href="#l1f4da">Rules</a></li><li><a href="#l62fd2">Rates</a></li><li><a href="#ld1a9a">How to apply</a></li><li><a href="#l23f7d">Further information</a></li></ul>
<div>

<div class="topic">

<div class="topic base_introduction">
<h2 class="topic base_introduction_title" id="l0b797">Introduction</h2>

<p>The Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade has introduced a new credit-card
sized Irish passport card which you can use for travel within the European
Union/European Economic Area (includes Iceland, Liechtenstein and Norway) and
Switzerland. For all other travel you must use your passport book, that is,
your normal passport.</p>

<p>The card has a maximum validity of 5 years. You apply for the card online or
using a smartphone app. </p>
</div>

<div class="topic base_rules">
<h2 class="topic base_rules_title" id="l1f4da">Rules</h2>

<p>You must be aged 18 or over when applying for the passport card. You must
hold a <a href="applying_for_or_renewing_an_irish_passport.html">valid Irish
passport</a> with at least 30 days validity. The personal details you provide
when applying must be exactly the same as those on your valid passport.</p>

<p>The card is valid for a maximum of 5 years or the remaining validity of your
passport.</p>

<p>If you intend travelling using your passport card, you must use the passport
card number when checking in online.</p>

<h3>Lost or stolen card</h3>

<p>If your passport card is lost, stolen or damaged, you should indicate the
loss, theft or damage of your card on the relevant section of the online
application form when reapplying for a new card.</p>

<p>If you are not reapplying for a new card you should notify the passport
service by <a href="https://www.dfa.ie/passportcard/contact-passport-card/">completing the
contact form</a>.</p>
</div>

<div class="topic base_rates">
<h2 class="topic base_rates_title" id="l62fd2">Rates</h2>

<p>The passport card costs €35. There are additional delivery costs for
applicants from outside Ireland of €5. Payment is made using a debit or
credit card.</p>
</div>

<div class="topic base_howtoapply">
<h2 class="topic base_howtoapply_title" id="ld1a9a">How to apply</h2>

<p>You can <a href="https://www.dfa.ie/passportcard/">apply for a passport card
online</a> or using a Department of Foreign Affairs and Trade app for
smartphones and tablets.</p>

<p>When making the application you need:</p>
<ul><li>Your valid passport</li>
  <li>Your photograph</li>
  <li>A debit or credit card</li>
</ul><h3>Photograph</h3>

<p>You have to supply a photograph in digital form that is less than 6 months
old. It must meet the required standard:</p>
<ul><li>The background must be plain and light in colour (white or pale grey)</li>
  <li>Your head must be centred in the photo with front pose (head not
  tilted)</li>
  <li>You must have a neutral expression (mouth closed, no smiling)</li>
  <li>There must be no shadowing on the face or around the eyes</li>
  <li>You must ensure your eyes are clearly visible and not obscured by hair or
    glasses (you may remove your glasses)</li>
  <li>The colouring must be natural (photo not too bright or too dark)</li>
  <li>You cannot wear headwear unless worn for religious purposes</li>
  <li>You should not wear a uniform (civil or military)</li>
</ul><p>If scanning in a passport photograph it should be scanned at a high
resolution (minimum 300dpi) at full size.</p>

<h3>Track your application</h3>

<p>When you submit your application online you are issued with an 11-digit
application number. You can <a href="https://www.dfa.ie/passports-citizenship/track-your-passport/">track your
application’s progress</a> on the Department’s website using the
application number.</p>
</div>

<div class="topic base_wheretoapply">
<h2 class="topic base_wheretoapply_title" id="l23f7d">Further information</h2>

<p>You can find more information in the <a href="https://www.dfa.ie/passportcard/faq/">Department’s list of FAQs</a>. If
you have any queries you can:</p>
<ul><li>Email <a href="mailto:passportcard@dfa.ie">passportcard@dfa.ie</a></li>
  <li>Telephone +353 1 671 1633</li>
</ul></div>
